Business Brief -- National Telesystem Ltd.:
   Firm Submits Offer to Buy
   Government's Telesat Stake
As reported earlier, a group composed of Canada's major
telephone companies and Spar Aerospace Ltd. also submitted a
bid for the government's stake in Telesat, which operates
Canada's domestic satellite communications system. The 10
telephone companies together already own 41.6% of Telesat.
Terms of the group's bid weren't disclosed.
   The government is expected to choose the successful bidder
by March 31.